# Test 3 on the 2026-07-10 board. Gate for backlog #5 (MI smelting array as line muscle).
TITLE: Crafter face-to-hatch drives a Modern Industrialization machine
HYPOTHESIS: A crafter facing an MI input hatch with a processing pattern can push ingredients in and the output comes back to RS - MI machines are usable as on-demand craft targets.
STEP zach: Place/point a crafter at the MI machine's input hatch and slot ONE processing pattern (input -> MI output). Reply !ok <machine/recipe> when set.
CAPTURE: craftstate
STEP zach: Order one batch of that output. Watch the hatch accept inputs and the machine run. Reply !ok when output is back in RS, or !no <where it stopped: hatch refused / machine idle / output stranded>.
CAPTURE: queue craftstate audit
CHECK: Output returned to RS and the task completed. If the output strands in the MI output hatch, note which return path is missing - that defines the go/no-go for the MI smelting array idea.
